This branch is a response to Issue 317 on the official XCSoar Github. See
https://github.com/XCSoar/XCSoar/issues/317

To build kernel:

cd ${KOBOSRC}
make mrproper
cp ${XCSOAR}/kobo/kernel/N249.config ${KOBOSRC}/.config
make -j3 ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=arm-kobo-linux-gnueabihf- zImage ; echo $?
sudo dd if=./arch/arm/boot/zImage of=/dev/${SDCARD} bs=512 seek=2048 ; sync ; sync

To set the Kobo as "registered":

On the section that will be mounted on /mnt/onboard do

sqlite3 .kobo/KoboReader.sqlite

INSERT INTO user(UserID,UserKey) VALUES('1','');

Kobo reference material:

https://www.yingtongli.me/blog/tag/kobo/

Kobo parameters:

Latest Kobo Reader supplied kernel has a uname -a of:
Linux kobo 4.1.15-00089-ga2737fc02713 #34 SMP PREEMPT Fri Dec 27 17:47:13 CST 2019 armv7l GNU/Linux

The following are the discoverable variables:

'ntx_hwconfig -s -p /dev/mmcblk0 CPU' == mx6sll
'ntx_hwconfig -s -p /dev/mmcblk0 PCB' == E60K00
'ntx_hwconfig -s -p /dev/mmcblk0 PCB_LVL' == A
'ntx_hwconfig -s -p /dev/mmcblk0 PCB_REV' == 0x10
'ntx_hwconfig -s -p /dev/mmcblk0 RAMType' == LPDDR2
'ntx_hwconfig -s -p /dev/mmcblk0 RamSize' == 512MB
'ntx_hwconfig -s -p -d /dev/mmcblk0 FrontLight' == 0x01
'ntx_hwconfig -s -p /dev/mmcblk0 Wifi' = RTL8189
'dd if=/dev/mmcblk0 bs=512 skip=1024 count=1 | grep -c "HW CONFIG' == 1
